# ap_lo Diastolic blood pressure
# cholesterol 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# gluc 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# smoke whether patient smokes or not
# alco Binary feature
# active Binary feature
# cardio Target variable

# Escolher o melhor mtry

set.seed(123)
ctrl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", 
                     number = 10,
                     repeats = 3,
                     classProbs = TRUE,
                     summaryFunction = twoClassSummary,
                     search = 'random')
rfFit <- train(cardio ~ .,
      method     = "rf",
      trControl  = ctrl,
      tuneLength  = 15, 
      metric     = "ROC",
      data       = cardio_train_fil)

# Stacking
library(e1071)

# Nivel-0

# Embaralhando os dados
set.seed(123)
cardio_train_fil <- cardio_train_fil[sample(nrow(cardio_train_fil)),]

# Divide em 5 parte
folds <- cut(seq(1,nrow(cardio_train_fil)), breaks = 10,labels = FALSE)

# Regressão Logística

nb <- NULL
# Validação cruzada 10-fold
for(i in 1:10){
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- cardio_train_fil[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- cardio_train_fil[-testIndexes, ]
    fit1 <- naiveBayes(cardio ~., data = trainData)
    fit1.pred <- predict(fit1, newdata = testData)
    nb <- c(nb, fit1.pred)
}
nb <- as.factor(nb)
levels(nb) <- c("No", "Yes")

# Predições para o cj de teste
fit.nb <- naiveBayes(cardio ~ ., data = cardio_train_fil)
fit.nb.pred <- predict(fit.nb, newdata = cardio_test_fil[,!names(cardio_test_fil) %in% "cardio"])

# k-NN

library(kknn)
## 
## Attaching package: 'kknn'
## The following object is masked from 'package:caret':
## 
##     contr.dummy
knn <- NULL
# Validação cruzada 10-fold
for(i in 1:10){
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- cardio_train_fil[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- cardio_train_fil[-testIndexes, ]
    fit2 <- kknn(cardio ~., trainData, testData, distance = 1, k = 9)
    knn <- c(knn, fit2$fitted.values)
}
knn <- as.factor(knn)
levels(knn) <- c("No", "Yes")

# Predições para o cj de teste
fit.knn <- kknn(cardio ~., cardio_train_fil, cardio_test_fil, distance = 1, k = 9)

# Árvores de decisão

dt <- NULL
# Validação cruzada 10-fold
for(i in 1:10){
    testIndexes <- which(folds==i,arr.ind=TRUE)
    testData <- cardio_train_fil[testIndexes, ]
    trainData <- cardio_train_fil[-testIndexes, ]
    fit3 <- rpart(cardio ~ ., data = trainData, method = "class")
    fit3.pred <- predict(fit3, testData, type = "class")
    dt <- c(dt, fit3.pred)
}
dt <- as.factor(dt)
levels(dt) <- c("No", "Yes")

# Predições para o cj de teste
fit.dt <- rpart(cardio ~ ., data = cardio_train_fil, method = "class")
fit.dt.pred <- predict(fit.dt, cardio_test_fil[,!names(cardio_test_fil) %in% "cardio"], type = "class")

#Nivel-1
all_train <- cbind.data.frame(nb, knn, dt, cardio_train_fil$cardio)
colnames(all_train) <- c("nb", "knn", "dt", "class")

fit4 <- glm(class ~., family = binomial(link = "logit"), data = all_train)
all_test <- cbind.data.frame(fit.nb.pred, fit.knn$fitted.values, fit.dt.pred, cardio_test_fil$cardio)
colnames(all_test) <- c("nb", "knn", "dt", "class")
p <- predict(fit4, all_test[,-4], type = "response")
result <- as.factor(ifelse(p > 0.5, "Yes", "No"))
confusionMatrix(result, all_test$class, positive = "Yes")
